rating and\nshaping the traveling waves, the diffusive part of the entropy production rate\nhas a negligible contribution to the system's total entropy production rate.\nThe Hopf instability shows a more complex and colossal change in the energy\nprofile of the open nonlinear system than in the traveling waves. A detailed\nanalysis of BF instability shows a contrary nature of the semigrand Gibbs free\nenergy with discrete and continuous wave numbers for the traveling wave.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Nov 2021 06:38:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-12"}
